101.value: Your basic all leather apparel. Finely crafted from tanned brahmin hide.

201.value: Polished metal plates, crudely forming a suit of armor.

301.value: A self-contained suit of advanced technology armor. Powered by a micro-fusion reactor, with enough fuel to last a hundred years.

901.value: XVB01 a designation for a series of vertical take-off and landing (VTOL) aircraft. Gamazon Prime is written on the side of this hull.

1001.value: XVB01 a designation for a series of vertical take-off and landing (VTOL) aircraft. Gamazon Prime is written on the side of this hull.

1101.value: The information contained in this folder is highly valuable to certain people. Precious find.

1201.value: A tiny, but very useful thing if you need to pick some locks. It does, however, require some skill.

1301.value: Even in a post-nuclear world, there are many uses for it.

1401.value: A rocket with a large explosive warhead.

1601.value: Uhh, I don't know how did you get this but... congratulations.

1701.value: High tech armor, made out of advanced defensive polymers.

1801.value: Well, in the current circumstances, it will be hard to find a use for it.

2001.value: Pretty thick notebook. The pages are untouched. Could be useful for taking notes.

2301.value: A bunch of different low-quality metal parts. Might come in handy.

2401.value: A roll of gray adhesive tape used before the Great War to fix just about anything.

2501.value: A short screwdriver with plastic handle. It's not a good idea to use this as a weapon.

2601.value: Old rags, smeared with gun oil. Not so useful.

2801.value: An old and dirty piece of cloth. Using this to deal with bleeding could have serious consequences.

3101.value: A brick of ammunition, .44 magnum caliber, hollow-points.

3201.value: A cylinder containing an extremely flammable liquid fuel for flamethrowers.

3401.value: A case of ammunition, .223 caliber, Full Metal Jacket.

3501.value: A brick of small, lightweight ammunition, standard military issue.

3601.value: A brick of small caliber ammunition, upgraded super-armor-piercing rounds.

3701.value: A rocket shell, with a smaller explosive, but designed to pierce armor plating.

3801.value: A small, self-contained energy storage unit.

3901.value: A medium sized energy production unit. Self-contained fusion plant.

4001.value: A healing chem. When injected, the chem provides immediate healing of minor wounds.

4101.value: Coins from a time before the war. There is an image of a sophisticated man imprinted on the other side.

4301.value: On old-style ice chest. The hinges are in good working condition.

4401.value: On old-style ice chest. The hinges are in good working condition.

4601.value: An average sized bag. Made from weaved brahmin hairs.

4701.value: A small kit containing basic medical equipment. Bandages, wraps, antiseptic spray, and more.

4801.value: A chemical solution that bonds with radiation particles and passes them through your system. Takes time to work.

4901.value: A bottle containing a home-brewed antidote for poison. A milky liquid with floating pieces of radscorpion flesh. Takes time to work.

5101.value: A high explosive, consisting of nitroglycerin mixed with the absorbent substance kiselguhr. Includes a timer.

5201.value: A Wattz Electronics C-Radz model Geiger Counter. Detects the presence and strength of radiation fields.

5301.value: A pillbox of mind-altering chems. Increases memory related functions, and speeds other mental processes. Highly addictive.

5401.value: A RobCo Stealth Boy 3001 personal stealth device. Generates a modulating field that transmits the reflected light from one side of an object to the other.

5501.value: This is a Vault-Tec water chip. They are typically packaged in groups of five to a box. Very expensive item nowadays.

5601.value: A set of dog tags, suitable to use as a proof of death of said person. Bring them to local law enforcment while their bounty is still up to claim a reward.

5701.value: A miniature microphone and transmitting device.

5801.value: A Wattz Electronics Holodisc tape. This particular tape looks to be into very poor condition.

5901.value: A Wattz Electronics C-U model motion sensor. Detects the movement of biological material over a distance of meters using a tuned radar device. Having one in your inventory will also help you avoid outdoor encounters (+20% Outdoorsman skill).

7101.value: A strange piece of fruit. No preservatives and no additional food coloring added.

7201.value: A briefcase, with a Made-in-the-USA label. Leather. Good condition.

7301.value: A set of books, containing information about different scientific fields.

7501.value: A tool set, containing various useful tools, including pliers.

7601.value: A study book on the field of electronics. A note on the cover says that it is for the "budding young electrician in everyone!".

7701.value: A Wattz Electronics Micromanipulator FingerStuff electronic lockpick. For defeating electronic locks and security devices.

7801.value: An image of a singer. Obviously, very old. The image has a felt coating that is still in good condition.

8001.value: A study book on the concepts and practical use of first aid skills.

8101.value: A cooked iguana, roasted in its own skin.

8201.value: A key. A key will open a particular lock.

8401.value: A set of locksmith tools. Includes all the necessary picks and tension wrenches to open conventional pin and tumbler locks.

8501.value: A chunk of C4, a military brand of plastic explosives. Highly stable, very destructive. Includes a detonator.

8601.value: A book on the methods and ideals of Scouting. Very practical information regarding outdoor life.

8701.value: Highly advanced steroids. While in effect, they increase strength and reflexes. Very addictive.

9001.value: A basic backpack, with optional carrying straps.

9101.value: This brown bag contains instruments and chems used by doctors in the application of their trade.

9201.value: The severed tail of a radscorpion.

9301.value: An average sized bag. Made from weaved Brahmin hairs.

9401.value: Patrolling the Mojave almost makes you wish for a nuclear winter.

9501.value: Shotgun ammunition. This particular ammo is marked: "12-gauge shells, not for use by children under the age of 3.".

9601.value: A electronic security key, color coded red.

9701.value: A electronic security key, color coded blue.

9801.value: A pile of junk parts. A little bit of everything.

10001.value: A model 2043B Radio Communicator, from the fine people at Wattz Electronics. Dependable, rugged, and camouflaged. With the optional RS-121 interface.

10101.value: A silver butane lighter, in good condition.

10201.value: A gun rag. A magazine devoted to the practical use of firearms, and the occasional biased review.

10301.value: Necklace made of animal teeth. Most likely a molerat. Person who made it was pretty skilled.

10401.value: A Wattz Electronics Play-It-For-Me tape recorder. Plays and records the standard 30 minute high density Record-It-Once tapes.

10501.value: A special key of some sort.

10601.value: A bottle of Nuka-Cola, the flavored softdrink of the post-nuclear world. Warm and flat.

10901.value: Anti-radiation chems to be taken before exposure. No known side effects.

11101.value: A brick of ammunition, .44 magnum caliber, full metal jacket.

11201.value: A beautiful golden urn, with the name "Harriet" inscribed on the front and ashes inside.

11301.value: A set of robes made from resistant mutated fibers. Someone with a sense of fashion has dyed them purple, or "hot pink".

11401.value: This framework of a robotic hand can be adapted to fit the Power Fist.

11501.value: Worn sheriff's hat. Time to try it on!

12201.value: Damn, it's heavy! Interesting, what's inside.

12401.value: Some type of home brewed beer.

24701.value: A wood shelf with miscellaneous items.

25201.value: This well-worn golden locket opens to reveal a charming picture.

25301.value: This chip controls the flow of power into a car's electric engines. Many drivers quickly burnt out this chip through frequent rapid acceleration. Still a valuable part to have-- if you only had a car to install it in.

25401.value: Some car-owners installed this regulator, that doubles your car's mileage between charges, but most drivers didn't care how much juice their cars consumed, after all, power's cheap and plentiful so why worry.

25501.value: This slightly crumpled piece of paper grants you access to all areas of Vault City, except the Vault itself, during daylight hours only.

25601.value: This is a set of false Citizenship Papers. They look authentic enough, but you doubt they could pass a serious inspection.

25701.value: This is an ancient time-piece known as a pocket watch. Time ran out for this keepsake, many long years ago.

25801.value: This is a Hydroelectric Magnetosphere Regulator.

25901.value: After Burner is a powerful methamphetamine chewing gum that stimulates the central nervous system. The initial euphoric rush rarely lasts more than a few minutes, but during that time, the user is filled with a rush of energy & strength.

26001.value: This antidote cures the addiction effects of Jet.

26101.value: A Red Ryder BB gun with the name 'Jonny' scratched on the stock.

26201.value: An old pair of sturdy rubber work boots. They look durable enough to keep out sludge, at least for a while.

26301.value: This is a message from the leader of the Slags to the townspeople of Modoc.

26501.value: This heavily padded leather jacket is unusual in that it has two sleeves. You'll definitely make a fashion statement whenever, and wherever, you rumble.

26601.value: This hand-held radio doesn't work but it looks as though it's still in pretty good condition. Some of its parts could probably be salvaged for use in other radios.

26701.value: This relic of the Vault was probably used to contain some sacred sacrament. The Holy number 13 is emblazoned on the side of this precious link to your people's past, and hopeful future.

26801.value: Polyester resin billiard ball. It has the number '8' on it..

26901.value: A pile of broken metal parts from the insides of a very unlucky robot.

27001.value: A bunch of 12Gauge slugs. They seem to have been hand loaded.

27101.value: The plentiful flower that forms the base for the powder of healing.

27201.value: The rare root that gives healing properties to the powder of healing.

27301.value: A very powerful healing magic- though it will bring the feeling of sleep to your head.

27401.value: A piece of a power armor, severely damaged. Even if you had hundreds of them, it would enver be enough to build a working armor, but it could help with reconstructing one.

27501.value: A solid gold trophy. It's impossible to make out the inscription, but the material itself should still have a decent value.

27601.value: This is the dried and cured hide of a Gecko.

27701.value: This is the dried and cured hide of a Golden Gecko.

27801.value: A stone used to sharpen weapons.

27901.value: It appears to be a set of electrodes built into a head unit with a standard computer interface plug.

28001.value: Polyester resin billiard ball. It has the number '9' on it.

28201.value: A small jar containing a human eye suspended in some kind of liquid. The label says General Clifton.

28301.value: Polyester resin billiard ball. It has the number '10' on it.

28401.value: These smoked and dried chunks of beast-flesh remain chewy-licious and even somewhat nutritious for years, and years, and years...

28501.value: These are enormous pincers that once belonged to a big Radscorpion.

28601.value: A pile of firewood and kindling.

28901.value: This is a shovel for digging ditches and stuff.

29101.value: It's a popular comic book series that featured more outlandish melee feats of knights.

29201.value: For those special occasions. Laugh track included.

29301.value: Polyester resin billiard ball. It has the number '13' on it.

29401.value: A holodisk which supposedly has the location of Vault 13.

29601.value: Polyester resin billiard ball. It has the number '14' on it.

30101.value: This is a clipboard with the coolant report.

30201.value: The label on this holotape reads: "Gecko Economic Data." It's difficult to interpret most of the technical charts, tables, and formulae here, but the majority of the information seems to highlight the advantages of a Vault City -- Gecko alliance.

30301.value: The label on this holotape reads: "Gecko Reactor Performance Data." This disk contains a string of numbers that mean nothing to you. There sure is a lot of information here and it must be important to someone, somehow.

30401.value: This is a deck of cards for a collectible card game. Looks like it could be an expensive hobby if you got hooked.

30501.value: An electronic security key, color coded yellow.

30601.value: An electronic security key, color coded red.

30701.value: This is a small energy transformer usesd in high-power energy weapons.

30801.value: An impressive tool set made by "Snap-Off".

31001.value: A bottle of Gamma Gulp beer. It glows in the dark!

31101.value: A bottle of Roentgen rum. It glows in the dark!

31201.value: This is a Part Requisition Request form.

31301.value: Wooden cue. You need this to play pool. But can you?

31401.value: This is a Jimmy Hats brand condom, a very reliable brand. This one is ribbed for her pleasure.

31501.value: This is a Jimmy Hats brand condom, a very reliable brand. This one contains phosphorous green dye #2 and is slathered in spermicidal lubricant for added protection.

31601.value: This is a Jimmy Hats brand condom, a very reliable brand. This one contains phosophorous red dye #5 and has a yummy cinnamon bun flavor... or so you heard.

31701.value: This is a genuine Mary May brand cosmetics case.

31901.value: Wooden triangle rack for pool. Very important thing for the game.

32001.value: Polyester resin billiard ball. It has the number '12' on it.

32101.value: A human brain that has been enhanced by the addition of electronic and robotic attachments.

32201.value: A typical human brain. Normally they are found in human skulls. Yuck.

32301.value: A monkey brain. It's soft and squishy.

32401.value: Quite possibly a human brain. The color doesn't seem quite right and the left hemisphere of the brain has caved in on itself.

32501.value: A standard pair of gambling dice. It'd be cool to get a fuzzy pair for your car.

32601.value: A pair of loaded dice. Don't be flashing these around the casino.

32701.value: This is a hard boiled chicken egg painted with colored dyes.

32801.value: This black sphere is some strange precognitive device... a small window on the top seems to be able to predict the future! Pre-war humanity must have been geniuses to invent such a wonder!

32901.value: A strange organic concoction that could possibly reverse the Mutation Factor in humans.

33001.value: This is wreckage from a Vertibird. Looks like it crashed here months ago.

33101.value: This is the hard to find Issue 5 of Cat's Paw magazine. The pictures aside, this issue has a wonderful article on female anatomy.

33201.value: Lad's Life was a pre-War camping and hunting magazine aimed towards the young adult male demographic. Despite it being meant for pre-War enthusiasts, the magazine offers legitimate survival tips that can be applied to life right now.

33301.value: These pills are used by people with heart problems.

33401.value: A hypodermic needle full of powerful poison.

33501.value: A new synthetic drug, crude red powder pressed into pill form. Eerily resembled clotted blood.

33601.value: Thomas Moore asked you to take this brahmin hide briefcase to the Bishop family in New Reno. It is securely locked, and you can't seem to open it.

33701.value: This is the holodisk you got from Lynette.

33801.value: This is the holodisk you got from Westin.

33901.value: This holodisk contains reports of NCR caravan schedules and security information. It's addressed to Darion and signed "F". With this info, it's easy to see how the raiders have avoided capture.

34001.value: A set of very detailed plans for a Cybernetic Canine Guard Unit. With this and the right facilities, a person just might be able to build a robo-dog.

34101.value: The bearer of this document is Security Clearance A-Prime as authorized by the authority of the President of the New California Republic. It's signed by President Tandi.

34201.value: This pin says you're an official New California Ranger. Look -- it's got a code wheel and everything! Strange, how it made its way all the way to Arizona.

34301.value: A map of the surrounding area -- it won't help you much -- but there are code names on it for the Ranger safe houses in the north.

34801.value: An intact scorpion egg. Hopefully it doesn't hatch anytime soon.

34901.value: Seeking to steal market shares from RobCo's personal computing devices, VaultTec modified a cheap spin-off device of Chinese manufacture and released it under the sister company ValueTec. The resulting Cheap-Boy 1999c was intended to replace the PIP-boy 2000 as the default computer in the VaultTec Vaults, but the devices were only delivered to Arizona before the Chinese trade embargo put an end to the imports. While not as aesthetically pleasing as the PIP-boy, the ability to modify and enhance the Cheap-Boy has made it a popular choice for more pragmatic adventurers.

35001.value: The front cover of the magazine depicts racks of Tommy guns on the front cover, advertising its 12 full color pages and articles such as, .308: America's Greatest Ally, Top 5 Battle rifles Rated!, CZ-57 Minigun: New AND Legal!, and Flamers for Home Defense?.

35101.value: A magazine that dedicated to the do-it-yourself repairmen, with advice ranging from basic repairs to advanced projects. The magazine also reviewed various tools and had general advice articles for the amateurs, such as "Working a Job & What Tools to Keep In Your Toolkit" and "0 Appliance Repairs Tips".

35201.value: A computer-oriented magazine, focusing on the latest Pre-War programming topics.

35401.value: A set of papers for receiving resource package delivery at @lex zone@.

35601.value: A piece of scrap metal that can be broken down into smaller parts.

35701.value: These rounds seem to be hand-loaded and are not quite as powerful as .45ACP. At least they should work.

35801.value: Ammunition for Gauss weapons. The large size and high velocity of the round essentially nullifies any sort of armor along with the stopping power of a big round.

36101.value: Ammunition. This cartridge appears to be ammo for the HN Needler Pistol. Each 'bullet' is a small hypodermic designed to inject a target with its contents upon impact.

36201.value: Ammunition. This cartridge appears to be armor-piercing ammo for the HN Needler Pistol. The hypodermic tips are made of a strange alloy and are incredibly sharp.

36301.value: Ammunition. Caliber: 7.62x51mm used in NATO weapons.

36401.value: This is the drive mechanism for a robot.

36501.value: It is a large book, heavily damaged by the Great War or subsequent events.

36601.value: The case is locked using a combination lock. The sound it makes suggests that it contains several items. An entry on the top side of the case made with a marker indicates the owner's call sign. Somebody probably would want this item and you have a feeling the value of the contents are time sensitive.

37101.value: Ammunition. This cartridge appears to be stimulant ammo for the HN Needler Pistol. The needles are filled with combat sustaining agents to help injured soldiers stay effective.

37201.value: It is a large book, heavily damaged by the Great War or subsequent events.

37301.value: An electronic security key, color coded red.

37701.value: Miscellaneous computer parts with various functions. A computer geek's dream.

37801.value: A chocolate chip cookie. Its so yummy that it will bestow an enlightened state upon your mind!

37901.value: An enhanced version of the basic leather armor with extra layers of protection. Finely crafted from tanned golden gecko hide.

38001.value: Polished metal plates, finely crafted into a suit of armor.

38101.value: A superior version of Combat Armor with many improvements over the standard version.

38201.value: This flamethrower fuel uses an advanced super-burn mix.

38301.value: The cover of this book is slightly burnt and the name is illegible. This is a kind of fictional story in the romance genre. Spicy pictures included. Nice.

38401.value: A thick book that covers the history of antiquity. It's full of knowledge.

38501.value: This is a horror story about cursed King who changes into a huge and terrifying Lizard under cover of night. Delightful.

38601.value: A folder full of all sorts of useful information.

38701.value: A folder full of all sorts of useful information.

38801.value: A folder full of all sorts of useful information.

38901.value: This is a homemade awl. It's probably not as reliable as a real one, but it's better than nothing.

39001.value: A typical wrench used by mechanics.

39101.value: The beaker is a simple glass container for stirring, mixing and heating liquids commonly used in many laboratories.

39201.value: A small grey-colored glass jar used for containing specimen.

39401.value: A standard surgical instrument to temporarily stop bleeding during surgery.

39501.value: Anatomical tweezers. An excellent tool for delicate work.

39601.value: It is a large book, heavily damaged by the Great War or subsequent events.

39701.value: An organic seed-spike that the carnivorous plants spit at potential food or seed carriers.

40701.value: A "Big Frigger" Power Fist from BeatCo. Considered by many to be the ultimate weapon to use in unarmed combat. This one has upgraded power servos for increased strength. Powered by small energy cells.

40801.value: A small kit containing basic emergency medical equipment. Bandages, wraps, antiseptic spray, and more.

40901.value: This bag contains instruments and chems used by paramedics in the field. The tools contained are specifically designed for high trauma and emergency cases.

41101.value: This is the second generation Wattz Electronics Micromanipulator FingerStuff electronic lockpick. For defeating electronic locks and security devices. This Mark II version includes updated software and interface tools.

41201.value: You see a can of high-class lubricant. Great stuff for cleaning weapon.

41301.value: This is a temporary ID badge. It has a red stripe through it, which seems to indicate that you are a "Stables Researcher.".

41501.value: A set of spectacles for eye correction.

41901.value: You see a bundle of parts that are clearly labeled "GX-9 Air Purifier". Using your incredible deductive skills, you decide that they are probably parts for a broken air purifier.

42101.value: A Holy relic of godly might.

42201.value: This chip appears to be for some sort of large industrial machine. Beneath the dirt and dust, it appears to be in surprisingly good shape.

42601.value: A chunk of Uranium Ore, unrefined.

42801.value: A box of assorted medical supplies. Nothing an unskilled person can make use of though.

Vault City might be interested in this.

150001.value: Mounting a suppressor reduces the loudness of a weapon, but it still is far away from being silent by any stretch of imagination.

150101.value: By changing the flow of gas at the muzzle of a gun, the muzzle brake helps to bring down the muzzle for quick follow-up shots but as a side effect it increases the audible range of the weapon.

150201.value: The added weight and length of the barrel makes for a more accurate weapon but at the same time makes quick target acquisition a little more difficult.

150301.value: With a shorter barrel, less energy is imparted on the bullet, making long range shots harder but greatly helping in a CQB situation.

150401.value: A quality stainless steel chrome-lined barrel will take a long time to degrade and is always a good investment to make a gun more reliable.

150501.value: A light barrel improves the overall handling of a weapon but is inherently more fragile.

150601.value: If you don't like what you see when looking down your irons, put these ones on.

150701.value: Perfect for small range engagements and quick target acquisition, but only for as long as you don't drop your rifle on the concrete too often.

150801.value: These help quite a bit at night but don't accomplish a lot during daytime.

151201.value: A very useful tool for room-clearing, as long as it doesn't turn into hall-clearing.

151301.value: Useful for making sure you're not overlooking something or someone.

151401.value: A vertical frontgrip gives you some extra leverage to hold down the muzzle during full-auto and burstfire, but purists say that the traditional rifle grip leads to much better accuracy at long ranges, of course.

151501.value: This kind of grip can provide the shooter with a more natural way of gripping the weapon, bringing up the sight picture just a split second faster.

151601.value: Being able to adjust the stock's length to your liking makes for a much more convenient shooting experience, at least as long as you don't try to bash doors in with your stock.

151701.value: Smooth adjustments in length, a comfortable buttpad and a padded cheekriser provides you with all the long-range luxury you need.

151801.value: A hydraulic buffer will soften the recoil impulse and make it easier to continue firing accurately. At least as long as the oil doesn't freeze up or blow out in extreme temperatures.

151901.value: While a light and handy weapon is favorable, this kind of stock doesn't necessarily instill the greatest deal of confidence in its structural integrity under stress.

152001.value: A great way to turn your rifle into a handy little package if you don't need while making sure it's there for you should you need it at a moment's notice.

152101.value: If you afraid of running out of bullets, this stock will be a great stand-in club.

765101.value: Modern gauze bandage made of cotton. A plastic porous film prevents direct contact and minimizes wound adhesion. Useful to treat minor bleeding.

765201.value: A simple yet effective device, twisting the stick applies pressure on the skin and underlying tissues of the limb, temporarily occluding blood flow. Most effective when the patient is in a life-threatening state as a result of continuous bleeding.

765301.value: This simple-to-use automated external defibrillator uses computer technology to analyze the heart rhythm and advice the user whether a shock is required. Treats ventricular fibrillation or tachycardia by administering high joule shocks that depolarizes the heart muscle. Designed for use by lay persons, it is more time consuming and less effective than a manual defibrillator.

765401.value: This Lifepak 78 manual external defibrillator comes with a built in electrocardiogram reader to help with diagnostics. High joule shocks administered through paddles on the patient's chest allow normal sinus rhythm to be restored. Capable of treating a wider range of conditions than the automated external defibrillator, but require a more detailed medical knowledge to operate.

1400401.value: The oldest and weakest of the typical .30 caliber rifle cartridges used by the great powers in the 20th century, but still a .30 caliber.

1400501.value: This round was specifically designed for the US light rifle program in world war II. It's a good bit faster than other pistol rounds but does not quite compare to a .30 caliber rifle round.

1400601.value: Originally based on a similarly sized round made by mauser, the tokarev is definitely on the fast side when compared to its contemporaries.

1400701.value: The .357 Magnum is just a little bit longer than its little brother, the .38 Special, and revolvers in .357 can usually fire the .38's as well. Using .357 in a revolver built for .38 special is not advised however, as the chamber pressure is a good three times higher and will rip the gun apart.

1400801.value: A wimpy round by modern standards, the .38 Special was a common cartridge used in law enforcement services all over the world from the 1920's on.

1400901.value: Even though this round was designed in 1873, it remained popular on the civil market due to the iconic rifles that used this round like the "Trapdoor" Springfield.

1401001.value: This Cartridge has a perforated case to vent propellant gases backwards, cancelling out the recoil of the projectile.

1401101.value: One of the first true intermediate cartridges, designed to be small enough to be have managable recoil and muzzle climb while being powerful enough to be effective out to 300 meters.

1401201.value: For a time this was the most powerful handgun cartridge in the world. That time did not last long but it still is nothing to sneer at.

1401301.value: The most powerful handgun cartridge in the world, at least as far as mass production is concerned. Easily surpasses some 'Full Power' rifle cartridges in muzzle energy.

1401501.value: A cartridge designed during the first world war to use in upcoming Heavy machine guns for tanks and planes, hence the designation "Tank und Flieger"

1401601.value: Much like the other anti-tank and anti-material rifle rounds of other nations, this is a cartridge developed between the two world wars for the PTRD-41 and was later used in heavy machine guns.

1401701.value: An assortment of various blackpowder cartridges, powder and ball packaged together for quick reloading. These are not actually moddern cartidges, the paper just holds all the ingredients you need to reload a muzzle loader.

1401801.value: Used in the american civil war, these projectiles were much more accurate and deadly than standard lead balls fired from muskets due to the added spin stabilization, but the rifling also meant they took longer to reload.

1402001.value: Crudely made iron spheres, filled with explosives. Handle with care.

1402101.value: These were used in the American Civil War in the Spencer and other carbines. As carbines, they are designed for short range and don't have the power of a full length rifle or musket.

1402201.value: In this unique cartridge, the case extends over the top of the bullet, designed to expand upon firing to seal the cylinder gap on the Nagant revolver. This unique feature allowed the Nagant to be properly silenced.

1402301.value: A popular early smokeless powder revolver cartridge which would later spawn the .44 Magnum. Not quite as powerful as its big brother.

1402401.value: This cartridge was originally developed in the 1920's in Germany but was picked up by the russians to serve in their SVDK rifles. It is somewhat comparable to .338 lapua in terms of power, but less suited for long range shooting.

1402501.value: A very popular and cheap plinking round, the .22 Long Rifle has taught generations the fundamentals of marksmanship before one moved on to "proper" calibers.

1402601.value: "Wildey's Here!" It says so right on the box of these neatly packed small little magnum cartridges.

1402701.value: The Hale rocket was the first rocket to use vent holes cut at an angle to create spin stabilization, making it much more accurate than its predecessors like the congreve rocket. They were used to some effect in the American Civil War and thereafter.

1402801.value: The ammunition for the Ampulomet are glass spheres filled with incendiary liquid, propelled with a blackpowder charge.

1402901.value: Around the time of the development of the Fedorov Avtomat, large quantities of 6,5 Arisaka were purchased by the Russians and so it was decided to adapt the Fedorov to it instead of producing a new one.

1403001.value: These rockets were developed for military use by Robert H. Goddard, who worked tirelessly on maximum rocket fuel efficiency and would later build the first liquid fueled rocket, setting the stage for modern space travel.

1403101.value: The cartridge for the SIG MCX Spear achieves its high power through an exceedingly hot load and a chamber pressure, that would lead to critical failures on normal firearms. To compensate for this, the cartridge cases have been strenghted, which comes at additional cost and weight.

1403201.value: Designed to be as flat-shooting and fast as possible, the 7,5mm FK round is one of the most powerful handgun rounds, without producing borderline unpractical amounts of recoil.

1403301.value: Based on a standard 8mm mauser bullet, the massively oversized cartridge propels it at over 1200 meters per second, a good 30% faster than standard rifle rounds.

1403401.value: The Grosse Panzergranate 61 was designed and used by the Waffen-SS as a makeshift anti-armor weapon. Like other such grenades, it is propelled by a blank cartridge and contains a shaped charge warhead.

1403501.value: The 6,5x55mm Swedish round was one of the more successful 6mm rifle cartridges and lived on beyond the 21st century as a hunting round. It's less powerful than its 7mm and 8mm contemporaries but produces less recoil. This particular round is fitted with a roundnosed bullet rather than a spitzer round, however, leading to less armor penetration.

1403601.value: A single round for the 20mm Lahti anti-material rifle. After all, a single round should be enough for anyone, or anything.

1403701.value: This is a specially designed subsonic ammunition with a very heavy projectile, in order to achieve maximum power without breaking the sound barrier. It was designed for the silent sniper system in vietnam, but the local humidity and overall climate supposedly degraded its accuracy and the project was scrapped.

1503101.value: This last generation anomalous activity detector can be used to locate anomalous formations and has a color diode panel, which not only indicates the direction of artifacts, but also measures the distance to them.

1503201.value: A next generation scientific detection scanner. Thanks to three modernized detection chambers, the position of artifacts is shown on a special display screen. When closed, the device registers only radiation and anomalies.

1503401.value: The Cossacks-brand vodka is a clear distilled liquor composed of water and ethyl alcohol. Vodka is made from a fermented substance of either grain, rye, wheat, potatoes, or sugar beet molasses. Vodkafs alcoholic concentration usually ranges between 35 to 70 per cent by volume.
